color-contrast-1.title: Background and foreground colors do not have a sufficient contrast ratio.
color-contrast-1.description: Low-contrast text is difficult or impossible for many users to read. [Learn how to provide sufficient color contrast](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/color-contrast).

frame-title-2.title: `<frame>` or `<iframe>` elements do not have a title
frame-title-2.description: Screen reader users rely on frame titles to describe the contents of frames. [Learn more about frame titles](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/frame-title).

link-in-text-block-3.title: Links rely on color to be distinguishable.
link-in-text-block-3.description: Low-contrast text is difficult or impossible for many users to read. Link text that is discernible improves the experience for users with low vision. [Learn how to make links distinguishable](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/link-in-text-block).

  The link has no styling (such as underline) to distinguish it from the surrounding text

link-name-4.title: Links do not have a discernible name
link-name-4.description: Link text (and alternate text for images, when used as links) that is discernible, unique, and focusable improves the navigation experience for screen reader users. [Learn how to make links accessible](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/link-name).

target-size-5.title: Touch targets do not have sufficient size or spacing.
target-size-5.description: Touch targets with sufficient size and spacing help users who may have difficulty targeting small controls to activate the targets. [Learn more about touch targets](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/target-size).
